com.facebook.buck.cxx

Class IncludeLog

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.cxx.IncludeLog

  • public class IncludeLog
extends Object
    Specialized parser for preprocessed output produced by either g++ -E -dI file.cpp or clang++ -cc1 -E -dI file.cpp. This preprocessed output contains inclusion directives (because of `-dI`) as written in the source, followed by the a line marker referencing the full path to the included file itself. These are what we use to determine how an include like `#include "foo.h"` or `#include ` was resolved into `/absolute/path/foo.h` or `/some/other/path/bar.h`: that there was an `-I /absolute/path` or `-isystem /some/other/path`.
